<div class="section" id="module-DBUtil.MachineGroups">
<span id="dbutil-machinegroups-module"></span><h2>DBUtil.MachineGroups module<a class="headerlink" href="#module-DBUtil.MachineGroups" title="Permalink to this headline">¶</a></h2>
<dl class="class">
<dt id="DBUtil.MachineGroups.MachineGroups">
<em class="property">class </em><code class="descclassname">DBUtil.MachineGroups.</code><code class="descname">MachineGroups</code><span class="sig-paren">(</span><em>db</em><span class="sig-paren">)</span><a class="headerlink" href="#DBUtil.MachineGroups.MachineGroups" title="Permalink to this definition">¶</a></dt>
<dd><p>Bases: <a class="reference internal" href="#DBUtil.DBUtil.DBUtil" title="DBUtil.DBUtil.DBUtil"><code class="xref py py-class docutils literal"><span class="pre">DBUtil.DBUtil.DBUtil</span></code></a></p>
<blockquote>
<div>General description:</div></blockquote>
<p>This class has definition for functions that provides add /update/ delete        / search by entities in database for MachineGroups.</p>
<dl class="method">
<dt id="DBUtil.MachineGroups.MachineGroups.add_machine_groups">
<code class="descname">add_machine_groups</code><span class="sig-paren">(</span><em>group</em><span class="sig-paren">)</span><a class="headerlink" href="#DBUtil.MachineGroups.MachineGroups.add_machine_groups" title="Permalink to this definition">¶</a></dt>
<dd><p>General description:
Args:</p>
<blockquote>
<div>param1 (group) : This is the parameter which has the details for             the new machine group to be added in database.</div></blockquote>
<dl class="docutils">
<dt>Returns:</dt>
<dd>Returns Database entity id of the new MachineGroup created</dd>
<dt>Example :</dt>
<dd>add_machine_groups(group)</dd>
</dl>
</dd></dl>

<dl class="method">
<dt id="DBUtil.MachineGroups.MachineGroups.add_to_machine_groups">
<code class="descname">add_to_machine_groups</code><span class="sig-paren">(</span><em>object_id</em>, <em>id_machine</em><span class="sig-paren">)</span><a class="headerlink" href="#DBUtil.MachineGroups.MachineGroups.add_to_machine_groups" title="Permalink to this definition">¶</a></dt>
<dd><p>General description:
Args:</p>
<blockquote>
<div><p>param1 (object_id) : This is the id of the existing machine            group which we have to update.</p>
<p>param2 (id_machine) : This is the machine ID of the             existing machine we wish to add to a MachineGroup.</p>
</div></blockquote>
<dl class="docutils">
<dt>Returns:</dt>
<dd>Returns the count of records that has been                 updated successfully for a given MachineGroup .</dd>
<dt>Example :</dt>
<dd>add_to_machine_groups(id, id_machine)</dd>
</dl>
</dd></dl>

<dl class="method">
<dt id="DBUtil.MachineGroups.MachineGroups.delete_machine_groups">
<code class="descname">delete_machine_groups</code><span class="sig-paren">(</span><em>object_id</em><span class="sig-paren">)</span><a class="headerlink" href="#DBUtil.MachineGroups.MachineGroups.delete_machine_groups" title="Permalink to this definition">¶</a></dt>
<dd><p>General description:
Args:</p>
<blockquote>
<div>param1 (object_id) : This is the ID of the existing             machine group which we have to delete.</div></blockquote>
<dl class="docutils">
<dt>Returns:</dt>
<dd>Returns the count of records that has been deleted                 successfully for a given MachineGroup .</dd>
<dt>Example :</dt>
<dd>delete_machine_groups(id)</dd>
</dl>
</dd></dl>

<dl class="method">
<dt id="DBUtil.MachineGroups.MachineGroups.get_all_machine_groups">
<code class="descname">get_all_machine_groups</code><span class="sig-paren">(</span><em>filter_required=None</em><span class="sig-paren">)</span><a class="headerlink" href="#DBUtil.MachineGroups.MachineGroups.get_all_machine_groups" title="Permalink to this definition">¶</a></dt>
<dd><p>General description:
Args:</p>
<blockquote>
<div>param1 (filter_required) : This is the parameter using            which we can filter different machine groups.
It can be machine group name or Machine ID .</div></blockquote>
<dl class="docutils">
<dt>Returns:</dt>
<dd>Returns Database entity of MachineGroup for the given filters</dd>
<dt>Example :</dt>
<dd>get_all_machine_groups(name) or get_all_machine_groups(machineID)</dd>
</dl>
</dd></dl>

<dl class="method">
<dt id="DBUtil.MachineGroups.MachineGroups.get_machine_group_by_machine">
<code class="descname">get_machine_group_by_machine</code><span class="sig-paren">(</span><em>machine_id</em><span class="sig-paren">)</span><a class="headerlink" href="#DBUtil.MachineGroups.MachineGroups.get_machine_group_by_machine" title="Permalink to this definition">¶</a></dt>
<dd><p>General description:
Args:</p>
<blockquote>
<div>param1 (machine_id) : This is the machine_id which is part of a machine group.</div></blockquote>
<dl class="docutils">
<dt>Returns:</dt>
<dd>Returns Database entity of MachineGroup for the given machine_id</dd>
<dt>Example :</dt>
<dd>get_machine_group_by_machine(id)</dd>
</dl>
